### Section 4: Care Leader View (~15 min)

**Narrative shift**: "You've seen the associate experience -- now let's switch to what Lisa and Michelle live in every day. The supervisor and care leader view."

**Navigation**: Open a new tab or switch to your pre-staged analytics tab. Navigate within D365: **Customer Service workspace** → left nav → **Omnichannel real-time analytics** (under Service).

---

#### 4a Real-Time Dashboards

**Navigate to**: Customer Service workspace → left nav → **Omnichannel real-time analytics** (under Service). Alternatively: **Dashboards** → select *"Omnichannel Ongoing Conversations Dashboard"* from the view selector.

**Say**: "Now let me switch to what Lisa and Michelle would see day-to-day. This is the Omnichannel real-time analytics dashboard. Lisa -- today you're pulling reports from Salesforce for cases, a separate report from Genesys for telephony data, and spreadsheets for SLA tracking. That's three systems to answer one question: how is my team doing right now? Here it's one screen, real-time, no assembly required."

**Show** (point to each element on screen):
1. **Active conversations by channel** -- email, phone, chat breakdown. "You can see at a glance where your volume is right now."
2. **Agent availability grid** -- who's available, busy, away, offline. "No guessing who's logged in -- the system knows because telephony, chat, and routing are all one platform."
3. **Queue wait times** -- per queue. "See which queues have the longest wait. Is Zurn Technical getting backed up? Are Elkay orders moving?"
4. **SLA compliance rate** -- if the SLA chart is visible. "First response and resolution KPIs -- the same SLAs we set up earlier, tracked automatically."
5. **Conversation status breakdown** -- active, waiting, wrap-up. "This is your morning standup in one glance."

**Say** (Salesforce comparison): "In Service Cloud, you'd need to build a custom dashboard in Salesforce Reports, pull in Genesys data through an integration, and hope the timestamps line up. Here the telephony data, case data, and routing data are all the same system -- so the numbers are always right."

> **Tip**: If the dashboard looks sparse (demo environment with limited volume), say: "In production with your full team running, this lights up. Right now we're looking at our demo data, but the structure is exactly what you'd see at scale."

---

#### 4b Agent Performance Metrics

**Navigate to**: From the real-time dashboard, click the **Agent** tab or navigate to **Omnichannel historical analytics** → **Agent** view.

**Say**: "Benton, you asked about performance metrics -- handle time, wait time, call duration. All of that is captured natively here because the phone, email, and chat all run through one platform. You don't need to pull a report from Genesys for talk time, a separate report from Salesforce for case metrics, and then reconcile them in Excel. One system, one source of truth for every metric."

**Show** (point to these if visible):
- **Average handle time** by agent or channel
- **Average wait time** for customers in queue
- **Conversations handled** per agent (daily/weekly)
- **Active vs. idle time** breakdown
- **Transfer rate** -- how often agents escalate or transfer

**Say** (supervisor daily workflow): "Michelle, imagine your morning routine: you pull up this view, see who handled the most cases yesterday, who had the longest handle times, who transferred the most. That's your coaching conversation for the day -- data-driven, not anecdotal. And because WFM is integrated, you can see if someone had a long handle time because they were juggling training and cases on the same shift."

**Say** (wrap up): "The key here is convergence. Today you have data in Salesforce, data in Genesys, data in spreadsheets, and it takes days to build a picture. Here, every interaction -- phone, email, chat -- flows through the same system, so the numbers are real-time and trustworthy."

> **If the dashboard is sparse**: "In a demo environment the volume is limited, but I want you to see the structure. In production, with 14 agents across five shifts, this view gives you instant visibility that today requires pulling three separate reports."

---

